@startuml
title MyWallet System Design
left to right direction
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam packageStyle rectangle

actor "End User" as User

node "Desktop Environment" {
  package "money_track\nJava Swing App" as Desktop {
    [Swing Screens] as SwingUI
    [Service Layer] as Services
    [Repository Layer] as Repositories
    [JDBC DatabaseManager] as JDBC
  }

  database "SQLite\nmoney_tracker.db" as DesktopDb
  folder "App Data\nlogs + CSV exports" as AppData
}

node "Android Device" {
  package "mywallet_android\nNative Java App" as Android {
    [MainActivity] as AndroidUI
    [WalletDatabase\nSQLiteOpenHelper] as WalletDbHelper
  }

  database "SQLite\nmywallet.db" as AndroidDb
}

cloud "GitHub Actions CI" as CI {
  [Maven Tests] as MavenTests
  [Desktop Installers] as Installers
  [Android Debug APK] as Apk
}

User --> SwingUI : desktop workflows
User --> AndroidUI : mobile workflows

SwingUI --> Services : validate commands\nload summaries
Services --> Repositories : persistence contracts
Repositories --> JDBC : SQL queries and updates
JDBC --> DesktopDb : JDBC connection\nforeign keys enabled
Services --> AppData : CSV export\nlogs

AndroidUI --> WalletDbHelper : direct CRUD calls
WalletDbHelper --> AndroidDb : SQLiteOpenHelper\nforeign keys enabled

DesktopDb .. AndroidDb : same logical schema\nusers, budgets,\ntransactions, goals

CI --> MavenTests : mvn test
CI --> Installers : package desktop app
CI --> Apk : Gradle build
@enduml
